The system behaves like a circulating flow rather than a command chain.

3. Geometry of Instability
Instability arises when the translation membrane collapses or becomes asymmetric.
Common failure modes:
Membrane Bypass
O → S

Direct control without interpretation.
Examples:
authoritarian systems
brittle software coupling
neural miscoordination

Membrane Pinch (Bottleneck)
