9. The Play Clause
To prevent the framework from becoming rigid doctrine, a self-limiting principle is included:
If the framework begins to feel inevitable, sacred, or correct, it has stopped functioning as a tool.
The hypothesis is intended as a playable lens, not a rule set.

10. Conclusion
The Triadic Overlap Hypothesis suggests that stability in complex systems may emerge from balanced translation membranes between sovereign domains.
Rather than collapsing meaning into structure or structure into meaning, the membrane maintains parallel sovereignty while enabling interaction.
Whether this pattern reflects a fundamental property of complex systems or simply a useful metaphor remains open.
The purpose of the hypothesis is not proof but invitation to investigate recurring geometry across domains.

